12 Section 1. Section 75-2-111, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "75-2-111. Powers of board. The board shall, subject to the provisions of 75-2-207:
14 (1) hold hearings relating to any aspect of or matter in the administration of this chapter at a place
15 designated by the board. The board may compel the attendance of witnesses and the production of evidence at
16 hearings. The board shall designate an attorney to assist in conducting hearings and shall appoint a reporter
17 who must be present at all hearings and take full stenographic notes of all proceedings, transcripts of which will
18 must be available to the public at cost.
19 (2) issue orders necessary to effectuate the purposes of this chapter;
20 (3) have the power to issue orders under and in accordance with 42 U.S.C. 7419."
