14 Section 3. Section 75-2-207, MCA, is amended to read:
15 "75-2-207. State regulations no more stringent than federal regulations or guidelines --
16 exceptions -- procedure. (1) After April 14, 1995, except as provided in subsections (2) and (3) or unless
17 required by state law, Except as provided in subsection (2), the department may not adopt a rule to implement
18 this chapter that is more stringent than the comparable federal regulations or guidelines that address the same
19 circumstances. The department may incorporate by reference comparable federal regulations or guidelines.
20 (2) (a) The department may adopt a rule to implement this chapter that is more stringent than
21 comparable federal regulations or guidelines only if:
22 (i) a public hearing is held;
23 (ii) public comment is allowed; and
24 (iii) the department makes a written finding after the public hearing and comment period that is
25 based on evidence in the record that the proposed standard or requirement:
26 (A) protects public health or the environment;
27 (B) can mitigate harm to the public health or the environment; and
28 (C) is achievable with current technology.
